<para id="RM000000W8E00VX" category="C" type-id="302I1" name-id="ES29G-02" from="200601">
<dtccode>P0500</dtccode>
<dtcname>Vehicle Speed Sensor "A"</dtcname>
<subpara id="RM000000W8E00VX_01" type-id="60" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00005JS00000">
<name>DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>The speed sensor detects the wheel speed and sends the appropriate signals to the skid control ECU. The skid control ECU converts these wheel speed signals into a 4-pulse signal and outputs it to the ECM via the combination meter. The ECM determines the vehicle speed based on the frequency of these pulse signals.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="A079413E16" width="7.106578999in" height="2.775699831in"/>
</figure>
<table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1" pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="3">
<colspec colnum="1" colname="c1" colwidth="1.42in"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="c2" colwidth="2.83in"/>
<colspec colnum="3" colname="c3" colwidth="2.83in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>DTC No.</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>DTC Detection Condition</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Trouble Area</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>P0500</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="left">
<ptxt>Vehicle speed signal from vehicle speed sensor is cut for 0.14 sec. or more while cruise control is in operation</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>Vehicle speed sensor</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Vehicle speed sensor signal circuit</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Combination meter</ptxt>
</item>
